<H1>6.2 pp2latex and pp2sdf
</H1>


<P>
<CODE>pp2latex</CODE> and <CODE>pp2sdf</CODE> can be used for the preparation of printable output formats. PerlPoint file which have been written for <CODE>pp2html</CODE> should be readable by <CODE>pp2latex</CODE> and <CODE>ppsdf</CODE>.
</P>


<P>
<CODE>pp2latex</CODE>  is still relatively inflexible concerning document classes. It is possible to supply a template file which determines the document class and provides a certain setup, but there are not many examples. If you use images you should supply an <B>.eps</B> file for each <B>.gif</B> or <B>.jpeg</B> file. <CODE>pp2latex</CODE> will then automatically inlucde these Postscript files in the LaTeX output. For controlling the  size, you can use the <I>epsfxsize</I> or <I>epsfysize</I> parameter in the <CODE>\IMAGE</CODE> tag:
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
 \IMAGE{epsfxsize=14cm src=&quot;./images/PerlPoint-Structure.gif&quot;}
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>
